---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What kind of asphalt repair do you handle in Spanish Fork?', a: 'Pothole repair, crack sealing, patching around utility cuts, and full sections of failed asphalt. If the damage is limited to a section of your driveway or lot rather than the whole surface, repair is usually the more cost-effective option.' },
  { q: 'Does Spanish Fork\'s wind actually affect asphalt?', a: 'Indirectly. Spanish Fork Canyon is a well-known wind corridor, and strong sustained wind drives grit and debris into surface cracks, which speeds up erosion once asphalt starts to fail. Sealing cracks early matters more here than in more sheltered parts of the valley.' },
  { q: 'Do you pave new subdivisions on Spanish Fork\'s east bench?', a: 'Yes. Spanish Fork has grown quickly on its east bench and in areas transitioning from agricultural land to residential lots. We handle new driveway and road-base paving for that kind of growth, not just repair on older streets.' },
  { q: 'Do you do work near the fairgrounds or downtown Main Street?', a: 'Yes. That part of Spanish Fork has some of the city\'s older asphalt, both residential driveways and small commercial lots, and it\'s a regular area for our repair and patching work.' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Asphalt Repair in Spanish Fork, UT | J&C Asphalt"
  description="Asphalt repair, crack sealing, and driveway paving in Spanish Fork, UT. J&C Asphalt fixes potholes and failing pavement fast. Free quotes."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Spanish Fork, UT</span>
      <h1 class="section-title">Asphalt Repair in Spanish Fork, UT</h1>
      <p>Spanish Fork sits at the mouth of Spanish Fork Canyon, the main route east to Price and Carbon County, and it's known throughout Utah Valley for the sustained wind that funnels through that canyon. That wind drives grit and debris into any crack or seam in asphalt, which is one of the biggest reasons pavement here fails faster once it starts to go. We handle repair work built for exactly that problem, along with new paving for Spanish Fork's fast-growing east bench.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get a Repair Quote</a>
        <a href="/work" class="btn-outline">See Our Work</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="area-overview">
        <div class="area-image">
          <img
            src="/images/crew-work-3.jpg"
            alt="J&C Asphalt crew repairing a damaged driveway near Spanish Fork, UT"
            width="640"
            height="520"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="area-text">
          <span class="section-label">Why Repair Timing Matters Here</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Canyon Wind, Fast-Growing Neighborhoods</h2>
          <p>Spanish Fork's location at the canyon mouth means it deals with wind conditions that are noticeably stronger than most of the rest of Utah Valley. On healthy asphalt that's mostly a non-issue, but once a crack opens, wind-driven grit and debris work their way in and accelerate the damage. A crack that would sit stable for a season or two elsewhere in the valley can widen faster here.</p>
          <p>At the same time, Spanish Fork has grown quickly, with new subdivisions spreading across the east bench and land that used to be agricultural now being built out residentially. That growth means a real mix of work: repair on older Main Street-area and downtown driveways, and new installation on freshly graded lots further out.</p>
          <p>We assess every Spanish Fork job the same way: repair where it makes sense, full replacement where patching would just be a short-term fix.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Repair &amp; Paving Services</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">What We Offer in Spanish Fork</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-links-grid">
        <a href="/services/asphalt-paving" class="service-link-card">
          <h3>Asphalt Repair &amp; Paving</h3>
          <p>Crack sealing, pothole patching, and full-section repair or replacement.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/driveways" class="service-link-card">
          <h3>Residential Driveways</h3>
          <p>New driveway installation for east bench subdivisions and older lots alike.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/parking-lots" class="service-link-card">
          <h3>Parking Lots</h3>
          <p>Commercial and church lot paving near downtown and the fairgrounds area.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Repair vs. Replace</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Reading the Damage Correctly</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="neighborhoods-text">
        <p>Not every cracked or potholed section of asphalt needs to be torn out. In Spanish Fork specifically, we look at how far wind-driven erosion has spread from the original crack. If it's contained to a section, patching and crack sealing usually restores the surface for years without the cost of full replacement.</p>
        <p>Where we do recommend replacement is when the sub-base itself has failed, usually visible as sinking, widespread alligator cracking, or repeated potholes forming in the same spot even after patching. That's more common on older Main Street-area driveways than on newer east bench construction, since older base material wasn't always installed to today's standards.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Common Questions</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Spanish Fork Repair FAQ</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-grid">
        {faqs.map(item => (
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>{item.q}</h3>
            <p>{item.a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="area-bottom-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Get Your Spanish Fork Repair Assessed</h2>
      <p>Send us a photo or request a visit and we'll tell you honestly whether it's a repair or a replacement job.</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
        <a href="tel:+14354064640" class="btn-outline-red">Call (435) 406-4640</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .page-hero p { color: #666; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; max-width: 720px; }

  .section-pad { padding: 5rem 0; }
  .section-dark { background-color: #F2F5F2; }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  }

  .area-overview {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .area-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 520px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
    display: block;
  }

  .area-text h2 { margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .area-text p { color: #666; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .neighborhoods-text {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .neighborhoods-text p { color: #666; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

  .service-links-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .service-link-card {
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #C8CEC8;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .service-link-card:hover {
    border-color: #cd553f;
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }

  .service-link-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #121212;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .service-link-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(1, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .faq-item {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #C8CEC8;
    border-left: 3px solid #cd553f;
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: #121212;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .area-bottom-cta {
    background-color: #cd553f;
    padding: 5rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .area-bottom-cta h2 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #000;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .area-bottom-cta p {
    color: rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 520px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .area-bottom-cta .btn-outline-red { border-color: #000; color: #000; }
  .area-bottom-cta .btn-outline-red:hover { background-color: #000; color: #cd553f; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .area-overview { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
    .service-links-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 580px) {
    .service-links-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
